# Premium button (`.btn-premium`)

Shared global button style for **any** interactive control that should feel
premium and gold-accented. Not tied to checkout, discounts, or a specific feature.

## Use it when

- A button or link should stand out with the brand gold treatment
- You want a secondary / accent action beside a dark `--primary` CTA
- You need a compact chip-style control (offers, upgrades, "learn more", etc.)

## Do not use it when

- The action is the **main** page CTA → `a.hero-cta` (large pill, hero sections)
- You need a **neutral** nav/back control → `a.btn-pill`
- You need the **primary** checkout/pay action → dark `--primary` background

## Usage

Works on `<button>` and `<a>`. Add layout classes at the call site; `.btn-premium`
only owns look and interaction.

```tsx
<button type="button" className="btn-premium" onClick={onClick}>
  {label}
</button>

<Link href={href} className="btn-premium">
  {label}
</Link>
```

Combine with local classes for width, flex, or animation wrappers:

```tsx
<button type="button" className="btn-premium my-local-wrap" disabled={loading}>
  Save
</button>
```

## What you get

- Gold gradient (`--accent-secondary` → `--accent`), dark text (`--accent-cta-text`)
- Soft border, inner highlight, gentle shimmer (~3.2s)
- Hover lift, active press, `:focus-visible` ring
- `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` disables shimmer and transitions
- `:disabled` dims and blocks pointer

## Source of truth

- Styles: `app/globals.css` — `.btn-premium`, `a.btn-premium`, `@keyframes btn-premium-shimmer`
- First use: cart discount button in `app/[lang]/cart/CartCheckoutView.tsx` (`co-discount-btn` scoped copy)

## Rules for agents

1. **Reuse the class** — do not copy gradient/shimmer CSS into styled-jsx or one-off modules.
2. **Tune globally** — change `--accent*` tokens or `.btn-premium` in `globals.css`, not per page.
3. **Layout stays local** — width, flex, exit animations, spacing belong at the call site.
